content: so nice to see such a big crowd tonight
Sorry GM, Let me explain first.
Tomorrow will be our GGM Luwenzhe's birthday.congratulate!!! wish things are going all right with our GGM lu
I am very happy. Thanks all
The server gives us a surprise as my birthday gift :)
that was to get your full attention! :))
let's hope it was the only one
Ok, now ( for the second time ),
As you know, this is my first time in this job,
so I hope everyone is patient tonight :)
look forward to a nice lesson
the renju federation was founded only less than 1 year ago
you guys did a good job there
since Finland is such a small country,
we have only so few members currently
But, we have got a nice start
the very first Finnish Championship tournament was arranged
imagine, in China the number would be pretty different :)
For today's theme I chose one game from this historical tournament
I have also written an article of the tournament, that will be available to you all some day soon
BTW, SamSite was the champion of that tournament :)
Today, we will look at a game from final round
while I setup the position, you will get some exercise also :)

So, the game was : Morden vs SamSite
but I was greedy and chose blacks :)
everyone is familiar with this for sure ?
I will skip other possibilities here and go straight to the end of theory
it wasnt that far in my case =)
in your opinion, which color is better here ?
I see this 2 most often myself
and I have lost as black here also often :))
what moves do you know here for white ?
G4 is probably most played, yes
couple days later, we analysed this more at game server
and found, that white can get very comfortable,
but black with precise moves can get big advantage too
We will return to check some 24th moves later
Now, Jussi chose a move here,
that I had not met before
has anyone of you met this one earlier ?
I was surprised, so I needed to think carefully here
Finally, I decided to play maybe a safe move, G6
that it cuts white activities well
that I could maybe use to threaten 4-3 to I4 later
Yes, blocking down seems like wasting a move, because white can not continue the attack really
Instead, 27 up increases black power a lot
Now, points I11 and I4 seem extremely good for black, right ?
since white has no attack left,
it should block one of these threats
which one would you take out ?
So now, the logical way to continue as black would be I4
Black surely has lots of chances here
But I chose to straight way
Now, whtioe must decide again between 2 moves
probably all your suggestions can lead to win :)
so seems unnecessary to check further here
everyone sees, that black has so much threats here
Now, I wanted to find a way to play,
that would be safe and powerful :)
often in this variant, a move like K5 fails in my hands
One thing here puzzled me for a while,
I came to conclusion, that this is not threat, if black doesn't make pause move :)
you are all so fast to find it:(55
So I didn't need to worry about it
I make an attempt to unite lower side all the way up
Sorry if I am slow, I have very slow connection
black will always win if it takes j11
it reduces chances to connect to either side
so now black must try win in mainly one side
After careful check, I chose 33- L!0
should black make four first to L7 ?
You probably remember Ando's words about making fours? :)
Don't use it, if opponent can't take it
here, white L7 seems so risky
black power up is so big
So no need for four first
Here, comes the beauty of L10
How many points possible for block ?
seems only L8 and L11 block both vcf

at this moment I was getting a little hopeful that the attack might  eventually fail!! =)
we have to go pretty far
my bad, but it turned out to be a guite challanging game afterall =)
On board finding the win was not so easy
But, let's look quickly at this 26
if black can destroy the white materials in left side without losing the tempo, than quite promising in rght side.
This is what I have thought
so move 30 must be block on left
seems black will try same as earlier
to come up from right side
but now white can play K9
We will not analyze here more closely, because I am thinking of a homework from somewhere here :)
If white would've forgotten F6 totally
Looks anyway, that I4 is not best choice now
i dont know whether it is sure win,but enough good for black
I have seen some games like this
and they end up with black win
white may be able to live, if cut connections between two sides
win on one area, seems very hard
whether it is sure win or not,
this position is much more hopeful for white, than in the game
The same attack without G6 support
without G6 stone, K8 now is without the primary reason I made it
this is one choice, it is bit unknown, therefore black need to be careful
also, white can choose this one
Making new moves is often efficient
You know this from playrs like Sushkov, Chingin :)
Jussi chose bravely a new move
this time, I was lucky enough to find win
I have nothing more to say, I thank you all for coming today
I hope it was worth the while
thank you for a nice lesson.
thank you for the lesson, GM
maybe next time I will be better :)
thank you for giving so nice lesson...
